# Pinned third-party deps. Single source of truth — every build script
# resolves through scripts/lib/deps.sh, which clones the named repo and
# verifies HEAD matches the commit below. See AGENTS.md "Vendored Deps".
#
# When updating a dep:
#   1. cd <dest>; git checkout <new commit>; iterate; commit upstream
#   2. update the commit column here
#   3. run `scripts/update-deps.sh` on every checkout
#
# An out-of-band update (HEAD moved without bumping this file, or this
# file moved without running update-deps) is a build-time error.
#
# Fields are tab-separated:
#   name <TAB> repo <TAB> commit <TAB> ref-hint <TAB> dest
#
# - name      : short identifier used by build scripts (`dep_ensure NAME`)
# - repo      : git URL
# - commit    : full sha-1 of the pinned tip. Verified bit-for-bit.
# - ref-hint  : branch or tag the commit lives on; passed to `git fetch`
#               so we don't have to fetch every ref. Use "-" if unknown
#               (we'll fall back to `git fetch origin` and `--unshallow`).
# - dest      : checkout path, relative to the repo root.
#
# Tarball deps (talloc, libmd) are not listed here — their version is
# baked into the URL inside the build script, so version bumps trigger
# a fresh download by construction.

# name              repo                                                                  commit                                      ref-hint                       dest
libhybris	https://github.com/wmww/libhybris.git	1d74c6a7d84d4ad5d4ffe20265f0e33273ac3d82	master	deps/libhybris
